OL,3,CWhat is the difference between legal,
OL,4,Cillegal and irregular migration?
OL,6,FWhile the word migrants is used often,
OL,7,Fthere are two types of movement ` into
OL,8,Fthe country (immigration) and out of
OL,9,Fthe country (emigration).
OL,11,FIn 2024, an estimated 948,000 people
OL,12,Fimmigrated to the UK while 517,000
OL,13,Femigrated, according to the Office for
OL,14,FNational Statistics (ONS).
OL,16,FThe difference between these two
OL,17,Ffigures ` the number of people
OL,18,Fimmigrating minus the number of people
OL,19,Femigrating ` is what is known as net
OL,20,Fmigration.
