OL,6,FNet migration in 2024 therefore stood
OL,7,Fat 431,000 people.
OL,9,FThe Labour Government has accused
OL,10,Ftheir Conservative predecessors of a
OL,11,F"failed open borders experiment" which
OL,12,Fsaw a large rise in net migration in
OL,13,Frecent years, reaching 873,000 in 2022
OL,14,Fand 860,000 in 2023.
OL,16,FLabour has vowed to ensure a "properly
OL,17,Fcontrolled and managed" migration
OL,18,Fsystem.
