OL,3,CWhat is the difference between legal,
OL,4,Cillegal and irregular migration?
OL,6,FAny person who is moving or has moved
OL,7,Facross an international border or
OL,8,Fwithin a state away from his or her
OL,9,Fhabitual place of residence is a
OL,10,Fmigrant, according to the definition
OL,11,Ffrom the United Nations' International
OL,12,FOrganisation for Migration (IOM).
OL,14,FThis is regardless of the person's
OL,15,Flegal status, whether they have moved
OL,16,Fvoluntarily or not, what the causes
OL,17,Ffor the movement are and what the
OL,18,Flength of their stay is.
OL,20,F` Are most arrivals to the UK people
OL,21,Fwho have come here legally?
