OL,3,CWhat is the difference between legal,
OL,4,Cillegal and irregular migration?
OL,6,FNo. An asylum seeker is a type of
OL,7,Fmigrant. But there are other types,
OL,8,Fsuch as people who have been granted
OL,9,Fthe right to come and live in the UK
OL,10,Fon a visa for a specific period of
OL,11,Ftime to study or to work.
OL,13,FAsylum seekers have not been granted
OL,14,Fthe legal right to come to the UK;
OL,15,Finstead, they are people who have
OL,16,Ftravelled to the UK to claim asylum in
OL,17,Fthe country.
