OL,3,CWhat is the difference between legal,
OL,4,Cillegal and irregular migration?
OL,6,FUnder international refugee law, there
OL,7,Fis no requirement for asylum seekers
OL,8,Fto make a claim in the first safe
OL,9,Fcountry they arrive in after leaving
OL,10,Ftheir country of origin.
OL,12,FBut under UK law, those who have a
OL,13,Fconnection or travel through another
OL,14,Fsafe country before reaching the UK
OL,15,Fcould have their claim refused.
OL,17,FThere can be a variety of reasons for
OL,18,Fpeople to seek sanctuary in the UK,
OL,19,Fsuch as joining family already in the
OL,20,Fcountry or knowing some of the
OL,21,Flanguage.
